<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/391:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-30T14:00:00-05:00">September 30, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2951. Following cable just received from Ankara [<hi rend="italic">Istanbul</hi>] (No. 107 of September 28):</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text of telegram printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                            <p>Please consult at once with British authorities as to best means of
                                executing this arrangement with the British Government.</p>
                            <pb facs="0968" n="956" xml:id="pg_956"/>
                            <p>Advise upon quantities and grades that will be available (the Defense
                                Commission wants as much as it can get as soon as it can get it) and
                                terms of payment. Also please discuss shipping arrangements.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>